AGI -&nbsp; Israel is obliged to "do everything, creatively, persistently and with determination", in its power to ensure the release of hostages still held in Gaza. The Times of Israel writes this by giving these words to President Isaac Herzog. "Today at 6:29 we will remember the six months from the brutal terrorist attack and the terrible massacre," we read, referring to the exact time in which Hamas began to launch rockets on Israel on the morning of October 7. "You are months after the crime against our sisters and brothers, against our country, against humanity," he continues, calling the war against Hamas "heavy in days and heavy in blood."
&nbsp;
On the case of hostages, &nbsp; media attention is directed to the case of Elad Katzir, kidnapped by Hamas in the kibbutz Nir Oz on 7 October and killed during the captivity. His sister Carmit announced it, announcing with a Facebook post that the death of man was notified to the family and that his body, recovered in the Gaza Strip during a raid, was reported in Israel last night. "The Army spokesman will not tell you that the PM, the government and the Idf have no idea where the majority of the kidnapped are kept and whether they are alive or have been killed. He won't even tell you that they have no way to protect them, even when they know where they are," added Katzir's sister, underlining that the joint "would have been saved if they had reached a deal in good time." The woman accuses the Israeli government of "codardy": "Look in the mirror and see if your hands don't dribble from that blood." Elad Katzir's mother, Hanna, was kidnapped by Hamas in the kibbutz Nir Oz on October 7 and was released on November 24 at the temporary ceasefire mediated by Qatar and the United States. Elad's father, Rami Katzir, was massacred by Hamas during the raid in the kibbutz.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Meanwhile, anti-government demonstrations are held in Tel Aviv and Haifa as well as the smaller gatherings at national level, with the participation of many people in Cesarea, Herzliya, Kfar Saba, Ràanana and Karkur. In particular to Caesarea, where protesters demanded new elections and invited Benjamin Netanyahu to resign, the police arrested at least one person near the private residence of the premier. In the videos of that incident, you see the police dragging the woman away from a fence where protesters against the government gathered at the end of a march towards the police barricades around the residence.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Meanwhile, Hamas refused to "turn back" over his demands for a ceasefire in Gaza, but agreed to send a delegation to renew talks in Cairo this weekend. "Hamas confirms its adherence to the position presented on March 14 and will not draw us back from this position", we read in a note of the Palestinian group in which reference is made to the demands, which include a complete ceasefire in Gaza and the withdrawal of Israeli forces from Gaza. Meanwhile, the Gaza Strip health ministry managed by Hamas updated the budget of the victims of the war: the dead have 33.137, of which 46 in the last 24 hours, and the wounded 75.815. &nbsp;
.&nbsp;<br> &nbsp;

